==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opercle
<hw>O"per*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>opercule</ets>. See <er>Operculum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Any one of the bony plates which support the
gill covers of fishes; an opercular bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An operculum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opercula</ent>⟦br⟧
